CBN Office, Makurdi The Makurdi Branch of the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) has suffered from a fire incident, as a portion of the bank went up in flames in the early hours of Thursday. According to eyewitnesses, the fire was noticed at the back of the bank, which is located in the Old GRA area of Makurdi, Benue State. “It was around 7:00 am this morning that we noticed the fire at the premises of the bank,” a witness identified as Stanley said. Further information revealed that the fire started from the bank’s fuel dome and spread immediately, drawing the attention of some workers who immediately raised the alarm. When contacted, the Director of Benue State Fire Service, Donald Ikyaaza, confirmed the report and said that he received a distress call about the fire incident and promptly deployed his men to the scene. “It was actually a huge fire which started at the company’s fuel dome but my men rushed to the scene and put out the fire before it could spread to other parts of the bank,” Ikyaaza said. “Everywhere is calm now.”